The paper proposes a new approach for entity alignment in knowledge graphs using graph neural networks. This falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and specifically, machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) as knowledge graphs often involve textual information. Additionally, the paper deals with database-related issues such as schema heterogeneity, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques such as attention mechanisms, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
